emuInput.TitMainTitle: Mrs. Ossie Stevenson standing in her home at 101 East Jefferson Street, Northside
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 24, 1955, pg. A14, reads: "Car Caroms Off Pole Into Parlor - Sunday Shock - Mrs. Stevenson's peaceful Sunday morning was shattered after she heard a bang and found an automobile lounging in her living room.  She and her son, Samuel Stevenson were both in another room when the unwanted prospect arrived. - Harris Photo."
